        </ul>
      </div>
      <div id="MaintainAirways">
        <h3>Maintain Airways:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Head tilt Chin lift</li>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Make sure the patient has no spinal injuries before doing this
              technique.
            </li>
            <li>
              Tilt the patient’s head back by pushing down on the forehead.
            </li>
            <li>
              Using the tips of the index and middle fingers of the second hand
              lift the mandible at the chin, which lifts the tongue from the
              posterior pharynx.
            </li>
            <img
              class="img7"
              src="./resources/Headtiltchinliftmaneuv.jpg"
              alt=""
            />
          </ul>
          <li>Jaw thrust</li>
          <ul>
            <li>
              If the patient has a suspected spinal injury use this technique.
            </li>

            <li>
              Placing the index and middle fingers to physically push the
              posterior aspects of the lower jaw upwards while their thumbs push
              down on the cheek bones to open the mouth.
            </li>

            <li>
              Be gentle yet firm while doing this technique as its painful and
              too much pressure can dislocate the jaw.
            </li>
            <img class="img8" src="./resources/jaw-thrust.jpg" alt="" />
          </ul>
          <li>
            <a href="./videos#MaintainAirways"
              >Click here to watch a video.</a
            >
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div id="AED">
        <h3>AED:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Turn on the AED and follow the visual and/or audio prompts.</li>
          <li>
            Open the person's shirt and wipe his or her bare chest dry if its
            wet,and remove any metals on the person's body (watch, rings,
            bracelets, phones...)
          </li>
          <li>
            Attach the AED pads (Usually one on the upper right of the chest and
            the other on the lower left chest below the armpit), and plug in the
            connector (if necessary).
          </li>
          <li>
            Make sure no one is, including you, is touching the person. Tell
            everyone to "stand clear".
          </li>
          <li>
            Push the "analyze" button (if necessary) and allow the AED to
            analyze the person's heart rhythm.
          </li>
          <li>
            If the AED recommends that you deliver a shock to the person, make
            sure that no one, including you, is touching the person – and tell
            everyone to "stand clear." Once clear, press the "shock" button.
          </li>
          <li>
            Begin CPR after delivering the shock. Or, if no shock is advised,
            begin CPR.
          </li>
          <li>
            Perform 2 minutes (about 5 cycles) of CPR and continue to follow the
            AED's prompts.
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="./videos#AED">Click here to watch a video.</a>
